Robyn Pearce's body was found in an apartment block in Sea Point on 2 December. CAPE TOWN - A 27-year-old man has been arrested in connection with the murder of a Stellenbosch University student in Sea Point.Robyn Pearce's body was found in an apartment block on 2 December. The 20-year-old had been stabbed. The police's Andre Traut says, &quot;A 27-year-old man was arrested last night in connection with the murder of Robyn Pearce. He will appear in the Cape Town Magistrates Court on Monday.&quot; (Edited by Shimoney Regter)